This paper is about Open Information Extraction, which is a subfield of Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Information Retrieval (IR). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the evaluation of Open IE systems, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also deals with annotation guidelines and scoring systems, which are related to data management and databases, making cs.DB (Databases) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper uses statistical methods to compare different Open IE systems, which is related to machine learning and data analysis, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category.
